cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on visual object tracking, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a method that combines deep learning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning to train an agent to make decisions, which suggests that it could also be categorized as cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves decision-making processes, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
